stylometry: Standard Deviation is important because it allows you to measure the risk of the certain answers you receive in a mode.  It measures and displays this based on the mean of the problem.  When a company or business is doing a simulation or a risk problem it is very helpful for them to see what levle of risk they will be taking if they chose one of the answers they receive from the problem or another answer.  Some of the workers are risk takers while other are not so much.  Using this standard deviation allows these people to actually measure the actual risk of accepting certain models.
